OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Les Budding
OL,5,F"If you saw all these ships side by
OL,6,Fside fastened together you could walk
OL,7,Ffrom one side of the harbour to the
OL,8,Fother across these vessels. It was an
OL,9,Feye opener and we were seeing vessels
OL,10,Fwe didn't know existed - rocket-firing
OL,11,Fcraft.
OL,13,F"The whole of the upper deck was taken
OL,14,Fover with rockets."
OL,16,FHis landing craft, LCF 34, was
OL,17,Fspecially adapted to give anti-
OL,18,Faircraft support and offered covering
OL,19,Ffire for the first and second wave of
OL,20,Ftroops on Sword Beach.
