OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Les Budding
OL,5,FThe gunners on the landing craft were
OL,6,Fso busy and he remembers at one time
OL,7,Ffiring 486 rounds without stopping.
OL,9,FNormally gunners would have to stop
OL,10,Fbefore that, he said, because the
OL,11,Fbarrels would become red hot.
OL,13,F"There wasn't a lot of damage to us
OL,14,Fbecause they were concentrating on
OL,15,Fsoldiers on the beach," he added.
OL,17,F"I didn't actually see them being
OL,18,Fgunned down but I saw some bodies
OL,19,Flying on the beach afterwards.
